We’re Hiring: Junior Machine Learning Engineer

An exciting opportunity for freshers and early-career professionals passionate about data, artificial intelligence, and building intelligent systems. You’ll work with our data science team to develop, train, and deploy ML models that power real-world business solutions.

Key Responsibilities:
Assist in developing, training, and testing machine learning models
Work with Python, pandas, scikit-learn, and TensorFlow/PyTorch
Perform data preprocessing, feature extraction, and model evaluation
Support deployment and monitoring of models in production
Collaborate with senior ML engineers and data scientists on live projects

Requirements:

0–2 years of experience in machine learning or data science
Strong understanding of Python and libraries such as NumPy, pandas, and scikit-learn
Knowledge of supervised and unsupervised learning algorithms
Familiarity with deep learning frameworks like TensorFlow or PyTorch (preferred)
Good grasp of statistics, data visualization, and problem-solving
Enthusiasm to learn and apply new ML techniques


We’re Hiring: Junior Full Stack Developer

An exciting opportunity for passionate freshers and early-career professionals to kickstart their journey in full stack development. Join our team to build dynamic, user-friendly web applications and work with both front-end and back-end technologies.

Key Responsibilities:

Assist in designing, developing, and deploying full stack web applications
Work with front-end technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and React
Develop RESTful APIs and backend logic using Node.js, Express, or Django/Flask
Work with databases like MySQL, MongoDB, or PostgreSQL
Collaborate with senior developers on debugging, testing, and code optimization
Participate in code reviews and maintain documentation

Requirements:

0–2 years of experience in web or software development
Good knowledge of front-end frameworks (React, Angular, or Vue.js)
Familiarity with backend frameworks (Node.js, Django, or Flask)
Basic understanding of databases, REST APIs, and Git version control
Strong problem-solving skills and a desire to learn modern web technologies
Understanding of responsive design and UI/UX principles is a plus
